Uses of Package
icontrol.drivers

  • Packages that use icontrol.drivers 
    Package Description
    icontrol
    This package contains the main Framework of the Instrument Control (iC) program (iC-Framework)
    icontrol.drivers
    This package contains the classes to support the different communication ports.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments
    Instrument-Classes for virtual Instruments; Template for new Instrument-Classes.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.agilent
    Instrument-Classes for Agilent Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.arduino
    Instrument-Classes for Arduino Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.cryomagnetics  
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.ekspla
    Instrument-Classes for Ekspla Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.eurotherm
    Instrument-Classes for Eurotherm Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.hp
    Instrument-Classes for Hewlett-Packard (HP) Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.keithley
    Instrument-Classes for Keithley Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.lakeshore
    Instrument-Classes for Lakeshore Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.srs
    Instrument-Classes for Stanford Research Systems (SRS) Instruments.
    icontrol.drivers.instruments.yokogawa
    Instrument-Classes for Yokogawa Instruments.
  • Classes in icontrol.drivers used by icontrol 
    Class and Description
    Device
    This is the base class from which all other Instrument-Classes should be derived.
  • Classes in icontrol.drivers used by icontrol.drivers 
    Class and Description
    Device
    This is the base class from which all other Instrument-Classes should be derived.
    Device.CommPorts
    Defines all implemented communication ports/protocols in any of the Instrument classes.
    Device.GenericInstrument
    Class that defines a generic Instrument.
    Device.GPIBcontroller
    Defines the supported GPIB controllers.
    GPIB_Driver
    Abstract class defining the required methods for a derived class to be recognized as a GPIB driver.
    GPIB_NI.gpib32
    Deprecated. 
    Defines the interface required by JNA to invoke the native library.
    GPIB_NI64.gpib64
    Defines the interface required by JNA to invoke the native library.
    GPIB_Prologix.ftd2xx
    Defines the interface required by JNA to invoke the native library.
    LAN_Driver
    "Driver" class to support network communication over TCP-IP.
    RS232_Driver
    "Driver" class to support RS232 communication in Instrument Control (iC).
    TMCTL_Driver
    This class provides access to the native code to access Yokogawa's TMCTL library.
    TMCTL_Driver.TMCTL
    Defines the interface required by JNA to invoke the native library.
